<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 07 at 7:21PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Bibb,
northeastern Peach and northeastern Crawford Counties through 800 PM
EDT...
At 721 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Skipperton, or near
Macon, moving west at 5 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Macon, Payne, Payne City, Lizella, Lake Tobesofkee, Jack Brown
Estates, Skipperton and Rutland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
